title: Earnings Watch: Facebook hopes to pick up where Google and Snap left off, in crazy earnings day
text: Alphabet Inc. and Snap Inc. have warned about severe downturns in the online-advertising market in the past week, and seen their stocks head higher.

title: Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg reportedly overhauled board to assert more control
text: he departure of key directors has helped consolidate decision-making power at the social networking giant, the Wall Street Journal reports.

title: WhatsApp eyes credit feature for users in India
text: WhatsApp, which began testing its mobile payments service in India two years ago, could offer at least one more financial service to people in its largest market: credit. In a filing with the local regulator in India, the company has listed credit as one of the areas it plans to explore in the country.

title: Facebook is hosting a virtual graduation with Oprah as commencement speaker
text: Oprah Winfrey will be everyone's graduation speaker this year, thanks to Facebook.

title: U.S. appeals court asks why Facebook encryption order should stay sealed
text: Federal appeals court judges asked prosecutors on Tuesday why a lower court could seal a ruling that absolved Facebook from having to wiretap a criminal suspect using one of the company’s encrypted services.

title: Facebook Restructures Its Security Teams
text: The social network displaced more than two dozen employees who work on security, as the company fights threats such as foreign meddling.

title: Facebook’s Libra Gets First Payment Company to Join Since 2019 Exodus
text: The Libra Association recently retooled its digital currency plans to appease regulators.

title: Will International User Growth Aid Facebook (FB) Q1 Earnings?
text: Facebook's (FB) first-quarter 2020 results are likely to reflect a burgeoning international user base and benefits from security initiatives amid disruption caused by the coronavirus pandemic.

title: As demand for digital advertising plummets, Google and Facebook could have shrinking revenues
text: Demand for digital advertising is shriveling after a decade of explosive growth amid the pandemic-fueled downturn.

title: The Best Earnings Charts of the 5 Big Tech Titans
text: The FAANG stocks and Microsoft are reporting earnings this week.

title: Facebook-backed digital currency project Libra has a new member
text: Checkout.com is the first payments firm to join Libra after Visa, Mastercard and Stripe pulled out over regulatory concerns.

title: Albion's Ware: Tech has been able to withstand COVID-19 pandemic, emerge as a utility
text: Jason Ware, partner and chief investment officer at Albion Financial Group, talks the tech sector and earnings amid the COVID-19 pandemic.
